item.title: [+891] Energizer Duo battery charger hides a Trojan
item.description: The Energizer Duo USB battery charger has been hiding a backdoor Trojan in its software that affects computers using Windows. According to Symantec the Trojan has probably been there since 10th May 2007.

item.title: [+620] Chile Earthquake Moved Entire City 10 Feet to the West
item.description: Precise GPS measurements from before and after the earthquake show that the magnitude 8.8 quake that struck near Maule, Chile Feb. 27 moved the entire city of Concepcion 10 feet to the west.

item.title: [+605] Chile, nine days later (PICS)
item.description: Nine days after an 8.8-magnitude earthquake killed hundreds of people in south-central Chile, relief efforts were beginning to reach those in need, rescue missions became recovery missions, and rebuilding is already under way. In the days since the February 27th quake, nearly 150 aftershocks have been recorded, including thirteen above magnitude 6.

item.title: [+584] Tax soda and pizza to cut obesity, researchers say
